title: No damage as small quake rattles upper skagit valley
author: Times Stafftimes News Services
text: CONCRETE, Skagit County      A quake measuring 2.3 on the Richter scale shook the upper Skagit Valley at 5:50 a.m. yesterday, but there were no reports of damage.     A spokesman for the University of Washington seismology lab said the quake was centered five miles northwest of Concrete.
